 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search This job has expired on Indeed Reasons could include: the employer is not accepting applications, is not actively hiring, or is reviewing applications Computer Vision and Machine Learning Engineer NCR Cambridge, MA Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description About NCR
 NCR Corporation (NYSE: NCR) is a leading software- and services-led enterprise provider in the financial, retail and hospitality industries. NCR is headquartered in Atlanta, Georgia, with 36,000 employees globally. NCR is a trademark of NCR Corporation in the United States and other countries. 
 
 Job Description
 Candidates will work on next-generation vision systems for enhancing the retail checkout experience and eliminating pain points for both customers and retailers.
 Areas of focus include:
 Facilitating the checkout process by applying computer vision and machine learning algorithms to automatically identify items at the checkout
 Localizing people and objects in the store, aisles, and checkout areas
 Preventing theft via anomaly detection
 Developing the algorithms, models, and methods for moving toward a fully frictionless checkout experience
 Prerequisites
 Candidates will have a Ph.D. in computer science, artificial intelligence, machine learning, applied math, or relevant field.
 They will have a strong practical nature and take pride in seeing their concepts turned into actual products that solve real-world problems.
 Candidates should have strong experience developing ML and CV approaches using Python.
 C++ experience and OpenCV experience are a plus.
 An affinity for, and background experience with, systems programming is a plus.
 Offers of employment are conditional upon passage of screening criteria applicable to the job.
 Full time employee benefits include  :
 Medical Insurance
 Dental Insurance
